Usage: setResizeLine [-help] [-clearAll] [-direction {H|V}] [ <points> ] [ -width <float> ]

-help                # Prints out the command usage
<points>             # The resize line point list. (pt list, optional)
-clearAll            # clear all resize line (bool, optional)
-direction {H|V}     # resize line direction (string, optional)
-width <float>       # resize line width (float, optional)